enumValues.description:
Indicates that the change pertains to a **Department** logical entity.

• In a delta query context, `DEPARTMENT` identifies that the returned record corresponds to a department logical object
(e.g., creation of a new department, update of department attributes, or removal of a department).

• In search/filter contexts, specifying `ChangeType: DEPARTMENT` will return only those changes where a department
was involved, ignoring changes to subjects, activities, etc.


.Example usage in a delta query:
[source,kotlin]
----
query {
  deltaChanges(
    between: {
      fromDateTime: "2025-01-01 01:00:00",
      toDateTime: "2025-01-01 01:15:00"
    }
    changeType: DEPARTMENT
    ) {
		changeType      # DEPARTMENT
		changeOperation # e.g., ADD, UPDATE, DELETE
		old             # JSON of the old data.
		new             # JSON of the new data.
	}
}
----

Indicates that the change pertains to a logical **Subject** entity (e.g., an academic subject or course offering).

• In a delta query context, `SUBJECT`  identifies that the returned record corresponds to a subject logical object.
(e.g., creation of a new subject, update of subject attributes, or removal of a subject).
• In search/filter contexts, specifying `ChangeType: SUBJECT` will return only those changes where a subject
was involved, ignoring changes to other entities.

.Example usage in a delta query:
[source,kotlin]
----
query {
deltaChanges(
  between: {
    fromDateTime: "2025-01-01 01:00:00",
    toDateTime: "2025-01-01 01:15:00"
  }
  changeType: SUBJECT
  ) {
    # Required Fields.
  }
}
----

Indicates that the change pertains to an **ActivityGroup** entity (e.g., a collection of related activities,
such as "LABS", "LECTURES", "WORKSHOPS", etc).

• In a delta query context, `ACTIVITY_GROUP`  identifies that the returned record corresponds to a activity group logical object.
(e.g., creation of a new activity group, update of activity group attributes, or removal of a activity group).
• In search/filter contexts, specifying `ChangeType: ACTIVITY_GROUP` will return only those changes where a activity group
was involved, ignoring changes to other entities.

.Example usage in a delta query:
[source,kotlin]
----
query {
 deltaChanges(
  between: {
   fromDateTime: "2025-01-01 01:00:00",
   toDateTime: "2025-01-01 01:15:00"
  }
  changeType: ACTIVITY_GROUP
  ) {
   # Required Fields.
  }
}
----

Indicates that the change pertains to an **Activity** entity  (e.g., a single class session, meeting, or event instance).

• In a delta query context, `ACTIVITY`  identifies that the returned record corresponds to a activity logical object.
(e.g., creation of a new activity, update of activity attributes, or removal of an activity).
• In search/filter contexts, specifying `ChangeType: ACTIVITY` will return only those changes where a activity
was involved, ignoring changes to other entities.

.Example usage in a delta query:
[source,kotlin]
----
query {
	deltaChanges(
		between: { fromDateTime: "2025-01-01 01:00:00", toDateTime: "2025-01-01 01:15:00" }
		changeType: ACTIVITY
		) {
			// Required Fields.
	}
}
----

